description: A weapon widely used from beginners to veterans. [Weight 5W]
name: Short Sword

description: A weapon preferred by skilled adventurers and soldiers. [Weight 8W]
name: Longsword

description:
Weapon that attacks with the weight of an iron lump attached to the tip.
Occasionally causes the opponent to faint. [Weight 10W]
name: Mace

description:
Lightweight weapon that is easy to handle even for women. Rarely causes the
opponent to bleed. [Weight 3W]
name: Dagger

description: A broken sword. Better than bare hands. [Weight 5W]
name: Broken Sword

description:
A sword believed to have been used by ancient warriors. Depending on its
condition, it may be sharper than weapons made in recent years. [Weight 8W]
name: Ancient Sword

description:
It has more of an aspect of being an art piece rather than a weapon. Luck
increases. [Weight 5W]
name: Golden Sword

description:
A sword with a legend that the god who controls fire used to wield. It sets the
opponent on fire when attacking. [Weight 15W]
name: Magic Sword Glenkaina

description:
A sword that unleashes immense attacking power through the power of a curse. In
exchange for its attacking power, it loses the ability to emit light and move
freely. [Weight 25W]
name: Demon God Sword Okotunushi

description: A short sword that brings various negative effects to the opponent. [Weight 3W]
name: Plague Mary

description:
A sword made of a very rare metal. Even great people who left their names in
history used to love it. [Weight 8W]
name: Mithril Sword

description:
A deadly weapon with spikes added to the tip for extra lethality. It can cause
both unconsciousness and damage from bleeding. [Weight 15W]
name: Morning Star

description:
A sharp and polished dagger that combines lightness and strength. Rarely causes
the opponent to bleed. [Weight 3W]
name: Sharp Edge

description: An inexpensive weapon made by carving wood. [Weight 5W]
name: Wooden club

description:
A bone-made club stained red with blood. It boasts high power, but is cursed
with the ability to decrease health every turn. [Weight 15W]
name: Thirst for Blood

description:
A weapon widely used from beginners to veterans. Supplied by the guild. [Weight
5W]
name: Short Sword (Provision)

description: A weapon that can deal significant damage to undead enemies. [Weight 8W]
name: Silver Sword

description:
A sword with a mysterious pattern engraved on the blade. The pattern faintly
emits light and makes a crackling sound. [Weight 10W]
name: War Sword

description:
Infantry carry a large dagger for auxiliary use. Unusually, the dagger also
provides a slight increase in defense. [Weight 3W]
name: Kushipos

description:
The legendary sword said to have been carried by an ancient king. A single
strike released from the blue shining blade delivers judgment to multiple
opponents. [Weight 8W]
name: Treasured Sword Eldard

description:
A weapon that combines offense and defense. Although its attack power is low,
its counterattack rate is high, making it truly effective in battles against
multiple opponents. [Weight 3W]
name: Jutte

description:
A weapon made from the head of a Guardian. Although it has lost its power
source, its eyes continue to faintly glow. [Weight: 15W]
name: Guardian's Head

description:
One of the brave warriors who stood up to overthrow the tyrannical king was a
dancer who received favor from the king. Evasion rate and critical hit rate
increase. [Weight 3W]
name: Dagger of the Stealthy Dancer

description:
The fallen enemy's armor becomes distorted and unusable, hence earning this
nickname. It reduces the opponent's physical resistance. [Weight 15W]
name: Garbage Collector

description:
The great sword that the orc had. It can mow down multiple opponents at once,
but it is thick and very heavy, so it can only be wielded with both hands.
[Weight 30W]
name: Bloodstained Oak Sword
